The paper discusses computational swarm intelligence, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. The focus is on the Artificial Bee Colony (ABC) algorithm, which is a nature-inspired optimization algorithm. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses social interactions within the swarm, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The use of network analysis to study the swarm's behavior suggests that the paper could also be classified under Complex Systems (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the emergence of complex behavior, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
